{"id":42218,"date":"2024-09-17T16:17:34","date_gmt":"2024-09-17T12:17:34","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=42218"},"modified":"2025-01-13T08:19:53","modified_gmt":"2025-01-13T04:19:53","slug":"warning-inheritance","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/09\/17\/warning-inheritance\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Wills: Warning to be fair with inheritance"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Verily, a man might act like the people of virtue for seventy years, but he enjoins injustice in his will, sealing his life with evil and entering the Hellfire. Verily, a man might act like the people of vice for seventy years, but he enjoins justice in his will, sealing his life with virtue and entering Paradise.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Abu Huraira said, \u201cRecite the verse if you wish, \u2018<strong>Such are the limits of Allah. Whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will enter gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. That is the greatest victory!<\/strong>\u2019\u201d (4:13)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 7728<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Ahmad Shakir<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u064a\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0644\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0639\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0644\u0650 \u0623